nua (excepto\\Nformulaciones IM de acción prolongada como benzatina o procaína).","guid":"UuqDGIeE4CnwqSQs3luxog","children":[]},{"id":"93","parent":"91","text":"• Eliminación renal → ajustar dosis en insuficiencia renal.","guid":"9jPda48P9VLy6zAQtRzkRg","children":[]},{"id":"94","parent":"91","text":"• Penetración al SNC con inflamación (penicilina G IV).","guid":"qhmZ8VnZmEgQ0ZZ5jn1GEQ","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"91","text":"• Penicilina V oral preferida a penicilina G (más estable en ácido,\\Nconcentraciones sistémicas ↑ que IV penicilina G).","guid":"2GcKLi-Rk9tQEBjKYSFkLg","children":[]}]},{"id":"96","parent":"0","text":"4. Usos\\Nclínicos:","guid":"purbGlsc1JoH5tUOKTw2Ew","children":[{"id":"97","parent":"96","text":"• No cubren/Siempre\\Nexcluidos:","guid":"FIFu1hqbd3qXZfFcH3stNQ","children":[{"id":"98","parent":"97","text":"• SAMR-SAMR","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"97","text":"• Neumococo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"100","parent":"97","text":"• E. coli","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"101","parent":"97","text":"• P. aeruginosa","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"102","parent":"96","text":"Más frecuente ","guid":"UA5Ot_8ROMoIeQA9__ZKvg","children":[{"id":"103","parent":"102","text":"• Faringitis estreptocócica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"104","parent":"102","text":"• Sífilis (1ra, 2da, latente)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"105","parent":"96","text":"• Espectro:","guid":"ALqDBLEol_XN9d0JzFim-Q","children":[{"id":"106","parent":"105","text":"• Infecciones por\\Nestreptococos grupo A:","guid":"vG8063AAUfok307_VVPCSA","children":[{"id":"107","parent":"106","text":"• Faringitis estreptocócica.","guid":"1NaQ3u9D-9RA3ASebcIbKA","children":[]},{"id":"108","parent":"106","text":"• Infecciones de piel o tejidos blandos\\N(cuando no se sospecha estafilococos).","guid":"EcaeUVlg83QiFRXdwUABTg","children":[]}]},{"id":"109","parent":"105","text":"• Infecciones enterocócicas susceptibles (con\\Naminoglucósido si se requiere actividad bactericida).","guid":"LTB_xmwDS701XY-PcB6Z3w","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"105","text":"• Meningitis por N. meningitidis, S. pneumoniae susceptible, y Listeria (penicilina IV).","guid":"0OYXFtqTMsCOYXHahqZJVw","children":[]},{"id":"111","parent":"105","text":"• Sífilis (penicilina benzatina o IV) → elección para todas las etapas.","guid":"xxOqlQDDm9GQBbu_HvYpbw","children":[]},{"id":"112","parent":"105","text":"• Enfermedad de Lyme (Borrelia).","guid":"Bwya7AtGhn2Ri7LWx0shZQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"113","parent":"0","text":"Efectos Adversos","guid":"S4PjQvQ5OJuNlOLjUEEJ1g","children":[{"id":"114","parent":"113","text":"• Reacciones de\\Nhipersensibilidad","guid":"LXnS26pvxatJJKOd4NTeaw","children":[{"id":"115","parent":"114","text":"• Reacción más grave: Anafilaxia mediada por IgE; incidencia solo 0.05% pero 5-10% fatal.\\NOtras reacciones mediadas por IgE: urticaria, angioedema, edema laríngeo, broncoespasmo.","guid":"x9EJ1u48fjKfpW5u2-OjeQ","children":[]},{"id":"116","parent":"114","text":"• Rash morbiliforme: Después de 72 horas, no mediado por IgE y no serio.","guid":"CY5-GXoxtueYnNCkA5Zpog","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"114","text":"• Reacciones alérgicas tardías graves: Anemia hemolítica Coombs-positiva, neutropenia, trombocitopenia (trombocitopenia\\Ninmune inducida por fármacos), enfermedad del suero, nefritis intersticial, hepatitis, eosinofilia, fiebre medicamentosa.","guid":"dHhYnt5CIp_dmiyO8xQfFg","children":[]}]},{"id":"118","parent":"113","text":"• Reacción de Jarisch-Herxheimer","guid":"TLlUJdOJtXqphbhypPiVwg","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"113","text":"• Altas concentraciones en LCR: Causan convulsiones. Reducir\\Ndosis en insuficiencia renal para evitar concentraciones altas.","guid":"relU-Py0vNfiIPUGVwINXA","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":119,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"General","folder":"Estudios Pivotales","filename":"Penicilinas Naturales-2024","id":"map_2488","resolved_references":[]}